lid; background-color: #ccc;">blah</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=3D"margin: =
16px 0;">Clover Health Inc., a health insurer backed by venture capitalist =
Chamath Palihapitiya, was swept up in meme-stock mania on Tuesday, posting =
a second day of wild gains as retail investors banded together to punish sh=
ort-sellers betting against the company.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Cl=
over rallied 86% to close at $22.15 in New York trading after briefly doubl=
ing intraday. The gains erased five months of losses in the stock -- which =
formed part of a broader selloff in Palihapitiya-backed companies -- in jus=
t two days. Trading volume in Clover was more than 29 times the three-month=
 daily average on Tuesday, with a record 718 million shares changing hands.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The sudden flurry of demand comes after re=
tail traders realized that short-sellers had been swelling their bets again=
st Clover, a move that left them vulnerable if the stock were to start rall=
ying. The stock=E2=80=99s story -- like many retail plays -- has left behin=
d fundamentals with shares trading above $20, that=E2=80=99s more than twic=
e the average analyst estimate.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;=
"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315.258690/=
aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jbG92ZXItaGVhbHRocy1zdG9jay1wcmljZS1=
zdXJnZXMtYWZ0ZXItYmVjb21pbmctbmV3LXJlZGRpdC1kYXJsaW5nLTExNjIzMTUyMTkwP21vZD=
1ocF9sZWFkX3BvczE/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8bc3bc85" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">And</a>:</p><blockquote><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The firm came under pressure =E2=80=A6 after Hindenbur=
g Research put out a report alleging that it misled investors, which Clover=
 Health=E2=80=99s management disputed. ...</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=
Some Reddit users are speculating that Clover Health could be the next shor=
t squeeze, which is characterized by a high level of its shares being sold =
short. =E2=80=A6=C2=A0=E2=80=9CApes who missed on $GME! Listen up, $CLOV is=
 ready to lift off!=E2=80=9D wrote one user who goes by u/pvr90 on Tuesday.=
 Ape is a nickname for buyers of AMC Entertainment Holdings Inc. shares, wh=
ich have been among the most actively traded meme stocks in recent weeks.</=
p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s a rough outline =
of the meme-stock cycle:</p><ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-=
left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There is =
a company.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Bad things happen: It g=
ets criticized for <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29tL2NvbnRlbnQvMWY5MTNhNWEtYTZlZi00Mz=
ZiLThiNTgtNGE0ODA0NjY1ZTcw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB135080dc" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> misleading investors a=
bout federal investigations</a>, it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGlua=
W9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDYtMDIvYW1jLWJyaW5ncy1vdXQtdGhlLXBvcGNvcm4/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB665aef56" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;">  operates movie theaters</a> that are shut in a pandemic,=
 it <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315.25869=
0/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMjUvd=
GhlLWdhbWUtbmV2ZXItc3RvcHM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB0be74622" itemprop=3D"S=
toryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration:=
 none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; b=
order-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  operates video-game s=
tores in malls</a> as games shift to being sold online, it literally <a hre=
f=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6=
Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjAtMDYtMTIvaWYteW91LXd=
hbnQtaGVydHotaGF2ZS1zb21lLWhlcnR6/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa49ad738" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  files for bank=
ruptcy</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The stock goes down, a=
nd valuation-focused investors sell it short, thinking it has further to go=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Retail investors on Reddit decid=
e that (1) it is actually undervalued, (2) the short sellers are evil and i=
mmoral and must be punished, (3) punishing the short sellers will cause the=
 stock to rocket to the moon and (4) this will all be pretty funny.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Lots of Reddit investors buy the stock, s=
hort sellers capitulate, the stock goes up.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bott=
om: 5px;">The stock goes up to way, way higher than it was in=C2=A0Step 2, =
or at any point in the company=E2=80=99s history.</li>=09<li style=3D"margi=
n-bottom: 5px;">A few people mildly and tentatively suggest=C2=A0that perha=
ps the stock=E2=80=99s current all-time-high stock price is not justified b=
y economic fundamentals.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Reddit is=
 not having it: Any time anyone says something even slightly critical about=
 the fundamentals, Reddit traders rush to buy stock and call options, pushi=
ng the price up even more.</li></ol><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way to=
 become a meme stock is not just to be=C2=A0<em>good</em>; companies don=E2=
=80=99t become meme stocks because Redditors endorse a widespread consensus=
 that they are good operators in attractive markets. The way to become a me=
me stock is to be=C2=A0<em>bad, then good</em>; companies become meme stock=
s because Redditors get mad at hedge funds for shorting them, so they buy t=
hem, so they go up, and it=E2=80=99s fun and more Redditors join in.[1]=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a lot to say about this cycle =
but here let=E2=80=99s talk about CEO incentives. There is a usual set of s=
tories=C2=A0that people tell about the incentives facing public-company chi=
ef executive officers. If you are the CEO, it is good for you if your compa=
ny grows quickly and makes a lot of money. It is good for you to prepare fo=
r the future, to anticipate trends, to move your company toward the next bi=
g thing. It is good for you to make money consistently, to report steadily =
rising profits. These things are good primarily because they make your comp=
any=E2=80=99s stock price go up, and since you are paid largely in stock an=
d own a lot of stock, you get richer as the stock price goes up. They are g=
ood secondarily because, with a high stock price and a good reputation, you=
 will have easy access to capital and you will be able to launch fun projec=
ts and make your company bigger and more important. And they are good for s=
ofter, more social reasons. If you report consistent rising profits analyst=
s will respect you and you will have nice interactions on earnings calls; y=
ou will be viewed as a good CEO and there will be flattering profiles of yo=
u in magazines. Your day-to-day life will be pleasant because people will t=
hink=C2=A0you are doing a good job; also the money is good.</p><p style=3D"=
margin: 16px 0;">Other things would be=C2=A0bad. If you have an accounting =
or regulatory scandal, that=E2=80=99s bad. If you operate a tired brand in =
a declining industry, that=E2=80=99s bad.=C2=A0Bankruptcy is obviously bad.=
 If your company performs poorly, it will attract short sellers. The short =
sellers will push down the price of the stock, which is bad for your wallet=
 (since you own a lot of stock). They will say mean things about you, which=
 you will find embarrassing. Earnings calls will be awkward and unpleasant.=
 As the stock declines due to your company=E2=80=99s poor performance, peop=
le will blame you for that performance, since after all you are the CEO. Ac=
tivist investors will buy stock and try to fire you to improve performance.=
 They might succeed. You=E2=80=99ll be out of a job, humiliated, with worth=
less stock.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Surely the public-company CEO h=
aving the most fun right now[2] is Adam Aron, the CEO of AMC Entertainment =
Holdings Inc., who has embraced his meme-stock status. (It has been <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6L=
y9naXptb2RvLmNvbS9hbWNzLWNlby1hcHBhcmVudGx5LWNvdWxkbnQtYm90aGVyLXRvLXB1dC1v=
bi1wYW50cy1mb3ItMTg0NzAzNzkzOA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb6a7679f" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">widely reported</a=
>=C2=A0that he wore no pants on a recent=C2=A0interview with a YouTube trad=
ing influencer;=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cli=
ck/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmVhZG1hcmdpbnMuY29tL3AvYXBlLWFybWllcy1h=
bmQtaW52ZXN0b3ItcmVsYXRpb25z/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1d5af27a" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Ranjan Roy argues</a>=
 that, if true, this was a good meme-stock investor-relations move, which i=
s plainly correct.) One reason that he is having a lot of fun is that he ow=
ns a lot of AMC stock and AMC stock is up 2,500% this year. Another reason =
that he is having a lot of fun is that he has=C2=A0<em>issued=C2=A0</em>hun=
dreds of millions=C2=A0of dollars of stock this year so that he can acquire=
 theaters, =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzL=
zIwMjEtMDYtMDIvYW1jLWJyaW5ncy1vdXQtdGhlLXBvcGNvcm4/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
C665aef56" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
>go on the offense</a>,=E2=80=9D and make AMC a bigger and more important c=
ompany. A third reason that he is having a lot of fun is that he is <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9hbWMtYm9zcy1hZGFtLWFyb24tYmFza3MtaW4tbWVtZS1z=
dG9jay1zcG90bGlnaHQtMTE2MjI3OTkwMDA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB347a8e85" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">a hero to an a=
rmy of online investors</a>, who <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/24099315.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly9tYXJrZXRzLmJ1c2luZXNzaW5zaWRlci5j=
b20vbmV3cy9zdG9ja3MvaG93LWFtYy1jZW8tYWRhbS1hcm9uLWVtYnJhY2VkLXRoZS1jb21wYW5=
5LW1lbWUtc3RhdHVzLTIwMjEtNi0xMDMwNDk2NDI3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3a63f9c9=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">call him=
</a> the =E2=80=9CSilverback=E2=80=9D; there=C2=A0is a lot to be said for b=
eing a beloved celebrity.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The way that Aron=
 got here =E2=80=94=C2=A0the way he got rich, the way he was able to raise =
a war chest to go after acquisitions, the way he became an internet celebri=
ty =E2=80=94=C2=A0was by running a company that was heavily shorted. That's=
 not the only thing that had to go his way, but it=E2=80=99s a big one. If =
analysts and institutional investors had been=C2=A0<em>thrilled=C2=A0</em>b=
y Aron=E2=80=99s response to the pandemic, if everything had gone right in =
AMC=E2=80=99s business, then =E2=80=A6=C2=A0I mean, AMC traded as high as=
=C2=A0$16.59 in April 2019, roughly a year before the pandemic; it traded a=
s high as $7.76 in February 2020, just before the pandemic hit it.=C2=A0Let=
=E2=80=99s say that, instead of plummeting in March 2020, AMC had responded=
 so well that it got back to its 2019 highs, and then=C2=A0<em>doubled=C2=
=A0</em>from there. That would get it to $33.18. It closed at $55.05 yester=
day. Getting memed was just=C2=A0<em>so=C2=A0</em>much better for AMC than =
performing well would have been.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I do not t=
hink that George Sherman, the lame-duck CEO of GameStop Corp., is having a =
ton of fun right now. He seemed pretty flummoxed by his meme-stock status t=
he whole time, and has only grudgingly raised capital. That capital will be=
 used not to pursue his own vision and expand his empire, but to pursue som=
eone else=E2=80=99s vision of closing stores and pivoting to online retail.=
 Also=C2=A0Sherman apparently has been pushed out by an activist. (He is ex=
pected to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24099315=
.258690/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzEzMjYzODAvMDA=
wMTE5MzEyNTIxMTIwMzA0L2QzMDc1OTlkZXg5OTEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB66e8=
4e85" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" style=3D"color: #00000=
