lockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A simple trading strategy of betting=
 against all horses classified as fast-sounding yields a return of approxim=
ately 2.9% before the commission but a negative return of =E2=88=921.6% aft=
er deducting the standard commission of 5% from Betfair. This finding could=
 be bracketed under the =E2=80=9Climits of arbitrage=E2=80=9D argument of G=
romb and Vayanos (2010) because the mispricing is not large enough to overc=
ome the transaction costs; thus, potentially misleading or false informatio=
n is not fully eliminated from prices. Nevertheless, this strategy generate=
s significantly larger returns than a random betting strategy in which appr=
oximately zero returns are achieved before commission and a negative return=
